{"id":5156,"date":"2026-03-07T18:37:39","date_gmt":"2026-03-07T13:07:39","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=5156"},"modified":"2026-03-07T18:37:58","modified_gmt":"2026-03-07T13:07:58","slug":"sb-11-10-34-elements-functions-of-lords-cit-acit-shaktis-the-better-choice-for-jivas","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/sb\/11\/10\/34\/","title":{"rendered":"SB 11.10.34 &#8211; Elements &#038; functions of Lord&#8217;s\u00a0cit,\u00a0acit\u00a0shaktis\u00a0&#038; the better choice for\u00a0Jivas\u00a0!\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"SB_11.10.34 - Elements &amp; functions of Lord&#039;s cit, acit shaktis &amp; the better choice for Jivas !\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/xfvAORMJ_2I?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam 11.10.34 | HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | ISKCON Chennai |&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>17<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;April 2021<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">O\u1e41&nbsp;namo&nbsp;bhagavate&nbsp;v\u0101sudev\u0101ya&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">O\u1e41&nbsp;namo&nbsp;bhagavate&nbsp;v\u0101sudev\u0101ya&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">O\u1e41&nbsp;namo&nbsp;bhagavate&nbsp;v\u0101sudev\u0101ya&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">nama&nbsp;o\u1e41&nbsp;vi\u1e63\u1e47u-p\u0101d\u0101ya&nbsp;k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-pre\u1e63\u1e6dh\u0101ya&nbsp;bh\u016b-tale&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">\u015br\u012bmate&nbsp;bhaktived\u0101nta-sv\u0101min&nbsp;iti&nbsp;n\u0101mine&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">namas&nbsp;te&nbsp;s\u0101rasvate&nbsp;deve&nbsp;gaura-v\u0101\u1e47\u012b-prac\u0101ri\u1e47e&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">nirvi\u015be\u1e63a-\u015b\u016bnyav\u0101di-p\u0101\u015bc\u0101tya-de\u015ba-t\u0101ri\u1e47e&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">jaya&nbsp;\u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya&nbsp;prabhu-nity\u0101nanda&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">\u015br\u012b-advaita&nbsp;gad\u0101dhara&nbsp;\u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Reading&nbsp;from&nbsp;Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam&nbsp;Canto&nbsp;11&nbsp;Chapter&nbsp;10&nbsp;Verse&nbsp;34.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>\u015aB 11.10.34<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">k\u0101la&nbsp;\u0101tm\u0101gamo&nbsp;loka\u1e25&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">svabh\u0101vo&nbsp;dharma&nbsp;eva&nbsp;ca&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">iti&nbsp;m\u0101\u1e41&nbsp;bahudh\u0101&nbsp;pr\u0101hur&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">gu\u1e47a-vyatikare&nbsp;sati&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Synonyms<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">k\u0101la\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 time;&nbsp;\u0101tm\u0101&nbsp;\u2014 the self;&nbsp;\u0101gama\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 Vedic knowledge;&nbsp;loka\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 the universe;&nbsp;svabh\u0101va\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 different natures of different living entities;&nbsp;dharma\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 religious principles;&nbsp;eva&nbsp;\u2014 certainly; ca \u2014 also;&nbsp;iti&nbsp;\u2014 thus;&nbsp;m\u0101m&nbsp;\u2014 Me;&nbsp;bahudh\u0101&nbsp;\u2014 in many ways;&nbsp;pr\u0101hu\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 they call;&nbsp;gu\u1e47a&nbsp;\u2014 of the modes of nature;&nbsp;vyatikare&nbsp;\u2014 agitation; sati \u2014 when there is.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Translation<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">When there&nbsp;is&nbsp;agitation and interaction of the material modes of nature, the living entities then describe Me in&nbsp;various ways&nbsp;such as all-powerful time, the Self, Vedic knowledge, the universe, one\u2019s own nature, religious ceremonies and so on.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Purport<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">One can experience the potency of the Personality of Godhead by&nbsp;observing&nbsp;how&nbsp;different species&nbsp;of life \u2014 demigods, human beings, animals, fish, birds, insects, plants, etc. \u2014 gradually evolve their natures and activities. Each species of life executes a particular process of&nbsp;sense&nbsp;gratification, and this function is called the dharma of the species. Lacking knowledge of the Personality of Godhead, ordinary persons catch a glimpse of the Lord\u2019s potencies in the above-mentioned manifestations.&nbsp;\u015ar\u012bla&nbsp;Madhv\u0101c\u0101rya&nbsp;has cited the following information from the Tantra-bh\u0101gavata. The Lord is called&nbsp;k\u0101la, or time, because He is the mover and controller of all material qualities. Because He is complete and perfect, He is called&nbsp;\u0101tm\u0101, or the Self; and He is the personification of all knowledge. The word&nbsp;svabh\u0101va&nbsp;indicates that the Lord fully controls His own destiny; and as the maintainer of&nbsp;everyone&nbsp;He is called dharma. One on the liberated platform can achieve unlimited bliss by worshiping the Personality of Godhead,&nbsp;whereas&nbsp;those who are ignorant of the Lord try to find happiness by concocting other objects of worship. If one stubbornly imagines that anything is independent of the Lord, one will remain in the grip of the illusory network of the Lord\u2019s potency. Seeing the inevitability of the destruction of material things, one is constantly fearful and perpetually&nbsp;laments&nbsp;in the darkness of ignorance. In such&nbsp;darkness&nbsp;there is no question of happiness. Therefore, one should never think that anything is independent of the Personality of Godhead. As soon as one considers anything to be independent of the Lord, one is&nbsp;immediately&nbsp;gripped by the Lord\u2019s illusory network, called&nbsp;m\u0101y\u0101. One should always remain humble and obedient to the Personality of Godhead, even when one is liberated, and thus one will achieve the supreme spiritual happiness.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">This is the conclusion on the modes of&nbsp;material nature.&nbsp;So, the statement here is that,&nbsp;when the&nbsp;prakrti&nbsp;transforms in&nbsp;various ways, then living entities describe the&nbsp;Lord&nbsp;in&nbsp;different ways, not understanding that the Lord is the cause of everything. So, here it gives a list of the different items that people designate as supreme, some of which are, in one sense, good, like&nbsp;<em>\u0101gama\u1e25<\/em>&nbsp;means the Vedas. So, yes, the Vedas&nbsp;represent&nbsp;the Supreme Lord.&nbsp;About&nbsp;loka&nbsp;or planets, of course,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;material. And we have these other items also, like&nbsp;dharma, also&nbsp;is&nbsp;comsidered&nbsp;to be material. And time, of course, is material.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, in this way, people concoct various ideas about what&nbsp;is the ultimate truth. So, these things are the Lord, but&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;indirectly the Lord. So, the Lord has his&nbsp;shakti&nbsp;called maya&nbsp;shakti or&nbsp;achit&nbsp;shakti.&nbsp;And this&nbsp;is considered to be&nbsp;non-different from the Lord, but also different from the Lord. So, it is different because it is&nbsp;achit, unconscious. So, time and&nbsp;karma and&nbsp;svabhava,&nbsp;etc,&nbsp;loka, these are all&nbsp;material.&nbsp;Of all these items, we can say&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;Atma is not&nbsp;[Laughs]&nbsp;material,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;spiritual, but those in the material world think&nbsp;I&#8217;m&nbsp;the body, so then again, the self also becomes material.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, in this way, a person in the material world views everything in terms of enjoyment. And as explained previously, this gives rise to suffering.&nbsp;So, on the other hand, if we have knowledge, then we understand the true position of these items. So, we know that time is a subtle aspect of&nbsp;maya&nbsp;shakti. And in the material world, it has past, present,&nbsp;future.&nbsp;And within time, there is creation and destruction. So, therefore, ultimately, time is a negative factor. To counteract that, the living entity, the human being at least, tries within time, within his lifetime, to get enjoyment.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">From&nbsp;the&nbsp;spiritual point of view, of course, time does not exist. In the spiritual world, there is no past, present,&nbsp;future. So,&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;world is quite different from&nbsp;material&nbsp;world.&nbsp;But within this concept of time in the material&nbsp;world, then,&nbsp;we think of times for material enjoyment. And there must be a beginning and end to that enjoyment. In the spiritual world, there is no beginning and no end to anything.&nbsp;So, therefore,&nbsp;the happiness&nbsp;is eternal.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, once we are stuck within time, we identify with&nbsp;a body. Then we&nbsp;do&nbsp;action to get the enjoyment.&nbsp;And if we are more fortunate, we will at least follow scriptures, that is karma scriptures to get the enjoyment. And&nbsp;as a result of&nbsp;all of this, we get a better body like a&nbsp;devata body. So, all of this is&nbsp;material&nbsp;world.&nbsp;And material living entities, material consciousness, then they work within these parameters, time,&nbsp;loka, body,&nbsp;etc,&nbsp;karma, to get their enjoyment. And all of this is resulting from&nbsp;gunas&nbsp;of material nature. And the living entity&nbsp;doesn&#8217;t&nbsp;see that behind all of this is the Lord, the controller of everything.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, the first work of the scripture, the duty of the scripture is to make the&nbsp;jiva&nbsp;understand that beyond all of these items mentioned here, we have&nbsp;atma&nbsp;and Supreme Lord. And then we can see that working with these different items here ultimately is meaningful. At the same time, we can see that since these are all emanating from the&nbsp;maya&nbsp;shakti, this energy of the Lord, there are positive elements in the spiritual world that resemble these things.&nbsp;So, with the&nbsp;maya&nbsp;shakti, the Lord creates&nbsp;all of&nbsp;these things mentioned in this verse. And with&nbsp;His chit&nbsp;shakti in the spiritual world,&nbsp;He&nbsp;creates similar types of things.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, we&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;have the material type of time, but we do have a resemblance to time.&nbsp;So, events happen and there is a beginning and middle and&nbsp;then&nbsp;an end to each activity.&nbsp;But there is no destructive element of time where over time,&nbsp;one gets old and dies.&nbsp;So, as we have bodies in the material world, we have bodies in the spiritual world.&nbsp;We have senses in the material&nbsp;world,&nbsp;we have senses in&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;world. We have activities in the material world such as&nbsp;dharma and&nbsp;karma and in the spiritual world, we also have activities. But in the spiritual world, all those activities are&nbsp;bhakti.&nbsp;So, technically they are called&nbsp;anubhavas. And as we have places and&nbsp;lokas&nbsp;in the material&nbsp;world, so&nbsp;we have places in the spiritual world like&nbsp;Vaikuntha&nbsp;and&nbsp;Goloka. But the places in the material world are&nbsp;temporary,&nbsp;the places in the spiritual world are eternal.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In the material world, we have the&nbsp;svabhava, which means the power which transforms a living entity into a&nbsp;devata or an animal etc. However, in the spiritual world, there is no change of body etc. However, we have the&nbsp;chit&nbsp;shakti of the Lord, expanding as the&nbsp;lila&nbsp;shakti, to create events in the spiritual world for the enjoyment of the Lord.&nbsp;So, of course, in the material world, we&nbsp;have the&nbsp;gunas, sattva,&nbsp;rajas and&nbsp;tamas. All of that is covered by ignorance. These&nbsp;gunas do not exist in the spiritual world.&nbsp;But we do have a type of spiritual ignorance. This is part of the&nbsp;chit&nbsp;shakti. So, we call this&nbsp;Yogamaya.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, by this power of Yogamaya, the&nbsp;jivas&nbsp;in the spiritual world are not aware of certain things. For&nbsp;instance, because of the&nbsp;Yogamaya&nbsp;potency,&nbsp;Krishna made&nbsp;Brahma see&nbsp;all of&nbsp;these Vishnu forms and then suddenly He disappeared.&nbsp;So, certain things are hidden from the vision of the&nbsp;jiva&nbsp;in the spiritual world. So, this is by&nbsp;the Yogamaya&nbsp;shakti. But this does not create any problem like&nbsp;the material&nbsp;ignorance.&nbsp;It is used by the Lord to increase the&nbsp;prema.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;it&#8217;s quite different from&nbsp;the ignorance of the material world.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">We see that,&nbsp;sometimes we describe the sleep of&nbsp;Vishnu&nbsp;as&nbsp;yoganidra. But then, if the Lord is sleeping, that is&nbsp;tamoguna. So, then our&nbsp;Acharyas&nbsp;explain that this sleeping is called&nbsp;yoganidra.&nbsp;And it is actually the Lord enjoying pastimes with&nbsp;His&nbsp;associates.&nbsp;So, it may look like sleep, but&nbsp;rather it&nbsp;is internal experience of bliss with devotees. So,&nbsp;rajoguna&nbsp;in the material world gives rise to passion and lots of activity.&nbsp;But of course, it is material activity for material enjoyment. So, in the spiritual world also, there is a&nbsp;very,&nbsp;there&#8217;s&nbsp;a&nbsp;lot of activity. There is eagerness to serve the Lord.&nbsp;So, this is not&nbsp;a bad quality&nbsp;in the spiritual&nbsp;world,&nbsp;it is&nbsp;a good quality. And it also is useful for increasing&nbsp;prema.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In the material world, we have&nbsp;sattvaguna, which creates heavenly planets.&nbsp;And of course, in the spiritual world, we&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;have that&nbsp;sattvaguna. But we often hear the word&nbsp;visuddha&nbsp;sattva. So, this means pure spiritual existence&nbsp;with&nbsp;no&nbsp;sattvaguna&nbsp;of&nbsp;the material world at all.&nbsp;So, like in the material world, we have gunas, so, we do have something like gunas in the spiritual&nbsp;world&nbsp;but they are also quite different.&nbsp;In any case, everything in the spiritual world and everything in the material world is because of the&nbsp;shaktis&nbsp;of&nbsp;Supreme&nbsp;Lord.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, the spiritual world is under the control of the Supreme Lord. And the material world is under the control of the Supreme Lord.&nbsp;So, in&nbsp;the material world, the&nbsp;jivas&nbsp;in ignorance cannot appreciate this.&nbsp;They think&nbsp;that,&nbsp;everything is here in the material world,&nbsp;operating&nbsp;without a Supreme Lord. So, that&#8217;s why this verse&nbsp;says,&nbsp;that&nbsp;they say&nbsp;that all of these different elements like the&nbsp;lokas, dharma and&nbsp;kala are&nbsp;Me or the Supreme Lord. In other words, by using these different things, they believe that they can get happiness.&nbsp;However, the only way they can get happiness is by realizing that&nbsp;all of&nbsp;these elements are arising from the&nbsp;maya&nbsp;shakti of the Supreme Lord.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And because they are all&nbsp;operating&nbsp;for giving&nbsp;enjoyment to ignorant&nbsp;jivas, then one can understand that&nbsp;ultimately&nbsp;we should get out of this situation completely.&nbsp;So, instead of being under the control of&nbsp;all of&nbsp;these material elements, it is better that we are under the control of the spiritual elements. So, the scripture reveals these things so that&nbsp;jiva&nbsp;can make&nbsp;a good choice.&nbsp;If the&nbsp;jiva&nbsp;does not have knowledge, it is very difficult to choose. So, therefore, I think as&nbsp;Bhaktisiddhanta&nbsp;Saraswati Thakur&nbsp;says, in the material world, what is the choice? It is like&nbsp;the&nbsp;drunkard,&nbsp;his choice is whisky or brandy.&nbsp;So, in the material world, you can choose one body or another body, one or in the other guna,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;all material world, all prison. Then we understand that there is a bigger choice.&nbsp;But it is up to the individual to choose.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Hare Krishna!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Q &amp;&nbsp;A :<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>1.) Maharaj, you mentioned with regard to the&nbsp;Acharyas&nbsp;mentioning about the&nbsp;yoganidra&nbsp;is the&nbsp;Lord is&nbsp;having&nbsp;His&nbsp;pastimes. How to appreciate in case of&nbsp;our deities&nbsp;like&nbsp;Lord Ranganatha&nbsp;or&nbsp;Ananta Padmanabha&nbsp;who are also&nbsp;kind of such&nbsp;a posture?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, all of these are representing the Lord lying on&nbsp;Ananta Sesha.&nbsp;And when&nbsp;He&nbsp;is lying down, obviously&nbsp;He&nbsp;is resting&nbsp;[Laughs]. And sometimes&nbsp;He&nbsp;is also sleeping. So, it says that for four months&nbsp;He&nbsp;goes to sleep on the milk ocean.&nbsp;That&#8217;s&nbsp;from, I think,&nbsp;oh,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;probably the&nbsp;whole&nbsp;chaturmasya&nbsp;period&nbsp;[Laughs]. At the end of&nbsp;chaturmasya,&nbsp;He&nbsp;wakes up. But that is the same type of sleep.&nbsp;Obviously, the Lord cannot be&nbsp;an ignorant. So, of course, in our sleep, we may have dreams. In the Lord&#8217;s sleep, it is not really a dream, but&nbsp;He&nbsp;is also having pastimes.&nbsp;But we cannot see them. So, that sleep is, we can say&nbsp;for,&nbsp;may be&nbsp;we can say it is&nbsp;for fooling the&nbsp;jivas&nbsp;[Laughs]. It gives&nbsp;an&nbsp;appearance of the Lord that&nbsp;He&nbsp;is something like a human being.&nbsp;But for pastimes, the Lord may take&nbsp;rest. But&nbsp;Lord&nbsp;is never put under&nbsp;tamoguna. So, within that sleep,&nbsp;then&nbsp;the Lord is still 100% conscious.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotee:<\/strong>&nbsp;Such pastimes are also known to these&nbsp;pure devotees of the Lord, Maharaj?&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;Well, if the&nbsp;jiva&nbsp;attains&nbsp;prema, then he can enter into any of these Lord&#8217;s pastimes.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotee:&nbsp;<\/strong>Maharaj,&nbsp;you mentioned&nbsp;prema&nbsp;bhaktas&nbsp;can&nbsp;enter into&nbsp;any pastimes? Any&nbsp;prema&nbsp;bhakta&nbsp;of any&nbsp;rasa&nbsp;can enter into any pastimes?&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH&nbsp;Bhanu&nbsp;Swami&nbsp;Maharaj:&nbsp;<\/strong>It&#8217;s&nbsp;up to the Supreme Lord and the qualification of the&nbsp;prema&nbsp;bhakta.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>2.)&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>Is there something like&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>vita<\/strong><strong>mo&nbsp;or&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>vir<\/strong><strong>ajo<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>like&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>visu<\/strong><strong>ddha<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;a<\/strong><strong>ssuming&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>&#8216;vi&#8217;&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>here means&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>vi<\/strong><strong>s<\/strong><strong>e<\/strong><strong>sha<\/strong><strong>?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Not commonly used, but we do have words like&nbsp;tama, then we have&nbsp;andha&nbsp;tama&nbsp;[Laughs], and&nbsp;I think there&nbsp;are a few of them describing the five different states of&nbsp;tamas.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>3.)&nbsp;Maharaj, if&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>we have the same qualities as the Lord has, then how is it that we have<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;envy&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>here?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">We&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;have&nbsp;all&nbsp;of&nbsp;the same qualities as the Lord. Jiva is&nbsp;tatastha.&nbsp;It&nbsp;can fall into&nbsp;ignorance.&nbsp;The Lord cannot fall into&nbsp;the&nbsp;ignorance. Then in ignorance, the&nbsp;jiva&nbsp;takes up a material body, develops all sorts of material desires, etc. None of these are in the Lord.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>4.) Maharaj&nbsp;mentioned that activities in the spiritual world are of&nbsp;devotion, bhakti.&nbsp;Is there a difference between the activities in the material world and&nbsp;in&nbsp;the spiritual world&nbsp;with regard to&nbsp;the pure devotees?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">As long as&nbsp;the devotee is in the material world, he has a material body limited by time and space. He deals with material objects in time and space.&nbsp;So&nbsp;there is&nbsp;a little difference.&nbsp;So, his experience of&nbsp;prema&nbsp;is also limited. So, when that&nbsp;devotee&nbsp;gives up his&nbsp;material body, then he can have full experience.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>5.) Maharaj mentioned that&nbsp;generally the&nbsp;devata&#8217;s body is&nbsp;better&nbsp;body. In the context of a living entity in this material world, he has an&nbsp;oppurtunity&nbsp;to go back within this lifetime because the duration is less than 100 or something. Whereas if someone takes to a devata body&nbsp;isn&#8217;t&nbsp;a disadvantage?&nbsp;Then&nbsp;in that context, how is it a better body?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Well, we can say that a&nbsp;devata, because he has a longer lifespan, he can practice serving the Lord for a longer time, and Brahma has such a long lifespan, he can have lots of time for sadhana.&nbsp;They are not afflicted so much by&nbsp;the old&nbsp;age&nbsp;and&nbsp;hunger&nbsp;and&nbsp;thirst, etc.&nbsp;So, therefore, they can spend more time on devotional activities.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>6.) Hare Krishna Maharaj,&nbsp;dandavat&nbsp;pranam. In the purport there is a statement that &#8220;Each species of life executes a particular process of&nbsp;sense&nbsp;gratification, and this function is called the dharma of the species.&#8221; Elsewhere in connection with&nbsp;<\/strong><strong><em>sa&nbsp;vai&nbsp;pu\u1e41s\u0101\u1e41&nbsp;paro&nbsp;dharmo&nbsp;[\u015aB 1.2.6]<\/em><\/strong><strong>&nbsp;or in other places, we see that dharma&nbsp;is the eternal occupational duty of the living entity. So, how&nbsp;to&nbsp;understand this Maharaj?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Here, the word&nbsp;dharma is taken in a more general sense. For instance,&nbsp;Prabhupada&nbsp;speaks of the&nbsp;dharma of water.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;dharma is to flow around, it has a sweet taste, quenches&nbsp;thirst. So, unlike human beings, animals&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;have a real&nbsp;choice of whether&nbsp;to&nbsp;follow&nbsp;dharma&nbsp;or not&nbsp;follow&nbsp;dharma.&nbsp;But they do have some common features.&nbsp;So, dogs have certain characteristics&nbsp;which&nbsp;distinguish them from cats. So, they have&nbsp;their&nbsp;particular food.&nbsp;And their particular way in which they live.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;that&#8217;s&nbsp;their&nbsp;dharma.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>7.)&nbsp;Have&nbsp;devatas got their position due to their fruitive activities in their&nbsp;previous&nbsp;lives&nbsp;which is&nbsp;contradicting to&nbsp;that they are&nbsp;Vishnu&nbsp;gupta&nbsp;sena,&nbsp;depend&nbsp;on&nbsp;Vishnu?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Oh, well, we have different people&nbsp;like&nbsp;people&nbsp;who&nbsp;go&nbsp;to swarga&nbsp;loka. Some people just go&nbsp;to swarga&nbsp;loka&nbsp;by doing&nbsp;karmas.&nbsp;They also do a little bhakti but not so much.&nbsp;However, to be a&nbsp;devata and enjoy as a&nbsp;devata enjoys, then,&nbsp;they also have to have devotional qualities to a greater extent.&nbsp;So, for instance, we have Brahma who is the greatest devotee.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;he has that position, one, because&nbsp;he&#8217;s&nbsp;a great&nbsp;devotee. And&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;on activities,&nbsp;which are,&nbsp;say&nbsp;the top of&nbsp;sattvaguna&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>8.)&nbsp;In our case, interaction with material modes of nature&nbsp;for us is unavoidable. So,&nbsp;how to minimize the agitation which is the resultant of that material modes&nbsp;of nature?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">As long as&nbsp;we live in the material&nbsp;world,&nbsp;we have&nbsp;a&nbsp;body and senses and they contact sense objects. But as a devotee we try to minimize our contact with material objects for&nbsp;maintaining&nbsp;the body&nbsp;etc, and we try to maximize using our body and senses for service.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>9.)&nbsp;Hare Krishna Maharaj. Maharaj, you have mentioned that devatas&nbsp;doesn&#8217;t&nbsp;have anger or thirst like that, so they have more opportunities to do bhakti there. But I heard some lectures that the demigods wanted to come to the material world because in<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>k<\/strong><strong>ali&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>y<\/strong><strong>uga the&nbsp;easy process&nbsp;is&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>Nama&nbsp;Sankirtana<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;and they can&nbsp;attain&nbsp;the devotional service. How&nbsp;we can&nbsp;understand this Maharaj<\/strong><strong>?<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Wherever there is&nbsp;mercy of the Lord,&nbsp;that&#8217;s&nbsp;the best place to be for spiritual advancement.&nbsp;So, if we have Caitanya Mahaprabhu manifesting with His devotees on earth planet, then that becomes the best place to get mercy.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotees:<\/strong>&nbsp;Grantharaj&nbsp;Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam&nbsp;ki&nbsp;jai!!!&nbsp;HH&nbsp;Bhanu&nbsp;Swami&nbsp;Maharaj&nbsp;ki&nbsp;jai!!!&nbsp;Srila&nbsp;Prabhupada&nbsp;ki&nbsp;jai!!!&nbsp;Nitai&nbsp;Gaura&nbsp;premanande&nbsp;Hari&nbsp;Haribol!!!&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam 11.10.34 | HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | ISKCON Chennai |&nbsp;17&nbsp;April 2021&nbsp; O\u1e41&nbsp;namo&nbsp;bhagavate&nbsp;v\u0101sudev\u0101ya&nbsp; O\u1e41&nbsp;namo&nbsp;bhagavate&nbsp;v\u0101sudev\u0101ya&nbsp; O\u1e41&nbsp;namo&nbsp;bhagavate&nbsp;v\u0101sudev\u0101ya&nbsp; nama&nbsp;o\u1e41&nbsp;vi\u1e63\u1e47u-p\u0101d\u0101ya&nbsp;k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-pre\u1e63\u1e6dh\u0101ya&nbsp;bh\u016b-tale&nbsp; \u015br\u012bmate&nbsp;bhaktived\u0101nta-sv\u0101min&nbsp;iti&nbsp;n\u0101mine&nbsp; namas&nbsp;te&nbsp;s\u0101rasvate&nbsp;deve&nbsp;gaura-v\u0101\u1e47\u012b-prac\u0101ri\u1e47e&nbsp; nirvi\u015be\u1e63a-\u015b\u016bnyav\u0101di-p\u0101\u015bc\u0101tya-de\u015ba-t\u0101ri\u1e47e&nbsp; jaya&nbsp;\u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya&nbsp;prabhu-nity\u0101nanda&nbsp; \u015br\u012b-advaita&nbsp;gad\u0101dhara&nbsp;\u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda&nbsp; Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp; Hare&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp; Reading&nbsp;from&nbsp;Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam&nbsp;Canto&nbsp;11&nbsp;Chapter&nbsp;10&nbsp;Verse&nbsp;34.&nbsp; \u015aB 11.10.34&nbsp; k\u0101la&nbsp;\u0101tm\u0101gamo&nbsp;loka\u1e25&nbsp; svabh\u0101vo&nbsp;dharma&nbsp;eva&nbsp;ca&nbsp; iti&nbsp;m\u0101\u1e41&nbsp;bahudh\u0101&nbsp;pr\u0101hur&nbsp; gu\u1e47a-vyatikare&nbsp;sati&nbsp; Synonyms&nbsp; k\u0101la\u1e25&nbsp;\u2014 time;&nbsp;\u0101tm\u0101&nbsp;\u2014 the self;&nbsp;\u0101gama\u1e2